WLC_RUN(3)                                               WLC CORE API FUNCTIONS

NAME

    wlc_run - run the main event loop

SYNOPSIS

    void wlc_run(void);

DESCRIPTION

    wlc_run() starts the main event loop created by the wlc_init(3) function.
    This is terminated with wlc_terminate(3).

RETURN VALUE

    None.

NOTES

    If wlc_run() is called before wlc_init() then nothing shall happen.

    If wlc_run() is called inside the event loop the behaviour is undefined.

ALSO SEE
    
    wlc_init(3), wlc_terminate(3)
